author: Times-News
title: Late overtime goal dooms Elon women in soccer
text: Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 12:44 AM Updated at 12:47 AM Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 12:44 AM Updated at 12:47 AM HARRISONBURG, Va. — James Madison’s Allison Bordell scored a header in the bottom right corner of the net with six seconds remaining in overtime to send the Dukes to a 1-0 Colonial Athletic Association victory against Elon in women’s soccer Friday night at University Park. James Madison (11-61 overall, 5-2-1 CAA) outshot the Phoenix 24-14. Ellen Forrest recorded six saves in goal for the Dukes. Alexis de Groot had a chance for the Phoenix (9-6-2, 1-5-1) with a few minutes left in the overtime period, but her shot was blocked by a defender. By Times-News
